  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently, the beacon node acting as a validator does not exit if a connection to a web3 PoW node cannot be established. This is a critical component of all beacon validator functionality, and we should issue a Fatalf if the connection cannot occur. Otherwise, users will run into panic conditions. This Fatal tlog should occur if we have some sort of `--validator` flag enabled.\r\n\r\n### In the Case the Beacon Node is Not Acting as a Validator\r\n\r\nWe will have an option for users to run a beacon node without being a validator for observation purposes. In this case, we should not throw a Fatalf if a web3 connection is not established.",
